---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Auftragstaktik | Ray Weiss"
  description="Auftragstaktik. A tactical OSINT command terminal with live frontlines, aircraft and ship tracking, air-defense envelopes, and auto-translated intel, in NATO symbology."
>
  <main class="px-6 py-24 lg:px-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1
        class="font-sans text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground lg:text-5xl"
      >
        Auftragstaktik
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-lg text-muted">
        A tactical OSINT command terminal. Frontlines, aircraft, ships, air
        defenses, nuclear sites, and conflict events on one map, in NATO
        symbology.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-body mt-16">
        <p>
          Eight togglable map layers across four theaters. Click any marker
          for detail panels and Wikipedia links. Dark or light basemap.
          Export the intelligence feed as JSON, CSV, or PDF. Historical mode
          replays 140,000+ archived conflict events from 1989 to 2023 with a
          year-gradient scrubbable timeline.
        </p>
        <p>
          The name is the German doctrine of mission-type tactics: give the
          objective, let subordinates execute. Ray gave Claude Code the
          objective and shipped the result in about two weeks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <th
                class="py-3 pr-6 font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
                >Layer</th
              >
              <th
                class="py-3 font-mono text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted"
                >What it shows</th
              >
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="font-serif">
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Tactical map</td>
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                Nine togglable layers: frontlines, aircraft, ships, air
                defense, installations, radar, nuclear, conflict events,
                density heatmap.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground"
                >Intelligence feed</td
              >
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                GeoConfirmed events plus auto-translated Telegram posts.
                Filter by source or severity, click to fly the map to
                location.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground"
                >Briefing generator</td
              >
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                Local LLM (Ollama) produces structured SITREPs with location
                summaries, faction breakdown, equipment losses, source
                attribution. Exports to PDF. Zero API cost.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Air defense</td>
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                OSINT-confirmed SAM and AD installations with engagement
                envelopes. S-400 at 400 km, Patriot at 160 km, Iron Dome at
                70 km.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Installations</td>
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                Thirty-five military bases, naval ports, HQs, logistics hubs,
                and chokepoints (Hormuz, Bab el-Mandeb, Suez, Malacca) across
                four theaters. Friendly or hostile affiliation marked.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Radar</td>
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                Twenty radar sites from Voronezh early warning (6,000 km
                range) down to coastal surveillance. Purple range rings show
                detection and tracking envelopes.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Nuclear / CBRN</td
              >
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                Known reactors, enrichment plants, weapons storage, and test
                sites. Yellow exclusion zones. CBRN keywords in events
                auto-escalate to critical severity.
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-4 pr-6 font-medium text-foreground">Historical mode</td
              >
              <td class="py-4 text-muted">
                140,000+ archived events from UCDP GED, 1989 to 2023, across
                five theaters (Yugoslav Wars, Gulf War, Iraq War,
                Afghanistan, Syrian Civil War). Cumulative playback with
                fatality-scaled markers.
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-body terminal-section mt-12">
        <h2>Data sources</h2>
        <p>
          All public OSINT. No paid APIs required. DeepState for frontlines,
          GeoConfirmed for verified events, adsb.lol for ADS-B aircraft,
          aisstream.io for AIS ships, Telegram channels (Rybar, DeepState UA,
          WarGonzo) auto-translated, UCDP GED for historical events.
        </p>

        <h2>Stack</h2>
        <p>
          Next.js 15, TypeScript 5.7, MapLibre GL for the map, Ollama for
          local LLM briefings. Public repo at <a
            href="https://github.com/lerugray/auftragstaktik"
            >github.com/lerugray/auftragstaktik</a
          >, MIT licensed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
